Drop -Werror from cet_set_compiler_flags.

gallery builds with DIAGS VIGILANT + WERROR. Under GCC 14 / C++20 (the conda
art-stack standard, vs upstream's C++17 default) VIGILANT's extra diagnostics get
promoted to hard errors. CXXFLAGS can't demote cetmodules'
add_compile_options(-Werror) (it lands after $CXXFLAGS), so drop the WERROR
keyword. See conda/potential_improvements.md (#2).
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -7,7 +7,6 @@
 cet_cmake_env()

 cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS VIGILANT DWARF_VER 4
-  WERROR
   NO_UNDEFINED
   EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic)
